---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service, All Webbed Labs"
  description="All Webbed Labs terms of service and conditions of use."
  noindex={true}
>
  <Header />
  <main>
    <section class="policy-section">
      <div class="policy-inner">
        <div class="policy-header reveal">
          <span class="section-label">Legal</span>
          <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
          <p class="policy-meta">Last updated: 16 July 2026</p>
        </div>
        <div class="policy-content reveal stagger-1">
          <p class="policy-lede">
            These Terms of Service govern your use of the All Webbed Labs website and any services or communications
            arising from your engagement with us. By using this site or submitting an enquiry, you agree to these
            terms. Specific project engagements are governed by a separate written services agreement signed by both
            parties, which prevails over any conflict with these general terms.
          </p>

          <h2>1. About Us</h2>
          <p>
            "All Webbed Labs" is a trading name of <strong>AW Labs Pty Ltd</strong> (the "Company", "we", "us", "our"),
            an Australian proprietary limited company. All engagements are contracted with the Company and are subject
            to Australian law.
          </p>

          <h2>2. Website Use</h2>
          <p>
            This website and its content are provided for general information about our services. Nothing on this
            website constitutes professional advice, an offer capable of acceptance, or a binding representation
            about the availability, price, timeline or suitability of any service. You must not use this website in
            any way that is unlawful, infringes the rights of others, interferes with its normal operation, or
            attempts to gain unauthorised access to any system, account or data.
          </p>

          <h2>3. Intellectual Property in Website Content</h2>
          <p>
            All content on this website, including copy, code, design, imagery, logos, video, and case-study material,
            is owned by AW Labs Pty Ltd or licensed to us. You may view and share the content for personal,
            non-commercial reference. Any other use, including reproduction, republication, framing, scraping,
            training of machine-learning models, or commercial use of any kind, requires our prior written consent.
          </p>

          <h2>4. Client Engagements and Project IP</h2>
          <p>
            The commercial terms, deliverables, timeline, pricing, warranties, and intellectual property arrangements
            for any client project are governed by the individual services agreement, statement of work or engagement
            letter signed for that project, and not by these Terms of Service. Our standard position is that, upon
            full payment of the agreed fees and unless expressly stated otherwise, ownership of custom deliverables
            transfers to the client, while we retain rights in any pre-existing tools, frameworks, libraries and
            know-how used to produce them.
          </p>

          <h2>5. Confidentiality</h2>
          <p>
            Information you share with us in enquiries, calls, briefs, or documents in connection with a potential or
            actual engagement is treated as confidential and will not be disclosed to third parties without your
            consent, except where disclosure is required by law or is reasonably necessary to seek professional
            advice. We can execute a mutual non-disclosure agreement on request, at no cost, before you share
            sensitive material.
          </p>

          <h2>6. No Warranty on Website</h2>
          <p>
            This website is provided on an "as is" and "as available" basis. To the maximum extent permitted by law,
            we make no warranty that the content is accurate, complete, current, uninterrupted, error-free, or free
            of viruses or other harmful components. You use this website at your own risk.
          </p>

          <h2>7. Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <p>
            To the maximum extent permitted by law, and subject to any non-excludable consumer guarantees under the
            Australian Consumer Law, our total liability arising out of or in connection with your use of this
            website is limited to AUD $100. We are not liable to you for any indirect, consequential, incidental,
            special or punitive loss, or for any loss of profit, revenue, data, goodwill, business opportunity or
            anticipated savings, however arising, whether in contract, tort (including negligence), under statute or
            otherwise. Liability for client engagements is limited as set out in the applicable services agreement.
          </p>

          <h2>8. Third-Party Links and Services</h2>
          <p>
            This website may contain links to third-party websites or reference third-party products and services.
            We are not responsible for the availability, content, security, or practices of any third party and
            provide such links for convenience only. Your interactions with third-party sites are governed by their
            own terms and policies.
          </p>

          <h2>9. Australian Consumer Law</h2>
          <p>
            Nothing in these terms excludes, restricts or modifies any right or remedy that cannot lawfully be
            excluded, restricted or modified under the Australian Consumer Law or any other applicable law.
          </p>

          <h2>10. Changes to These Terms</h2>
          <p>
            We may update these Terms of Service from time to time. The "Last updated" date at the top of this page
            reflects the current version. Continued use of the website after any change constitutes acceptance of
            the updated terms.
          </p>

          <h2>11. Governing Law and Jurisdiction</h2>
          <p>
            These terms are governed by the laws of New South Wales, Australia. You submit to the exclusive
            jurisdiction of the courts of New South Wales and courts competent to hear appeals from them for any
            dispute arising out of or in connection with these terms or your use of this website.
          </p>

          <h2>12. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            Legal enquiries: <a href="mailto:legal@allwebbedup.com.au">legal@allwebbedup.com.au</a><br />
            AW Labs Pty Ltd, 1 Ramsay Rd, Five Dock NSW 2046, Australia.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .policy-section { padding: 9rem 0 6rem; background: #0a0f0e; min-height: 80vh; }
  .policy-inner { max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 2rem; }
  .policy-header { margin-bottom: 3rem; }
  .policy-header h1 { font-family: 'Sora', sans-serif; font-size: 2.5rem; font-weight: 800; color: white; margin: 0.75rem 0 0.5rem; }
  .policy-meta { font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif; font-size: 0.875rem; color: #4a6359; margin: 0; }
  .policy-content h2 { font-family: 'Sora', sans-serif; font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 700; color: white; margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem; }
  .policy-content p { font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif; font-size: 0.9375rem; color: #4a6359; line-height: 1.75; margin: 0 0 1rem; }
  .policy-content a { color: #0d9373; text-decoration: none; }
  .policy-content a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  .policy-content strong { color: #cde0da; font-weight: 600; }
  .policy-lede {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    color: #cde0da;
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin: 0 0 2.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #1e2d28;
  }
</style>
